  "doc_id": "6826",
  "text": "We have provided here clear evidence supporting HGT(s) between E. huxleyi and EhV for seven genes probably involved in the biosynthesis of sphingolipids. Given the previously reported cotranscription of the viral genes [CITATION_1] ) and the validated enzymatic activity of the viral SPT [CITATION_2] ), all of these viral enzymes are likely to be functional. The prevalence of those genes in a wide range of host and virus strains and the pattern of their amino acid and DNA sequence conservation revealed by this study further support that these enzymes are functional in both E. huxleyi and EhVs.",
